Dele Ogunyemi, Warri The Delta State Government on Sunday announced that two of its officials – Secretary to the State Government, Mr Chiedu Ebie, and the Commissioner for Information, Mr Charles Aniagwu – had tested positive for COVID-19. This was contained in a statement by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor. Mr Olisa Ifeajika. It was said both officials had been on the frontline of the state COVID-19 task force. The statement said the two officials showed mild symptoms of the virus and consequently subjected themselves to the test. The statement added, “Both officials have been moved to an isolation centre where they are stable and responding well to treatment.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com